{
  "texts": [
    "DL-based approaches, have shown to be quite successful for several medical diagnostic tasks, outperforming human specialists in certain cases.",
    "However, the algorithms' black-box nature has limited their clinical use.",
    "Recent explainability studies have attempted to demonstrate the characteristics that have the most impact on a model's choice.",
    "Furthermore, interpretability findings are often based on a comparison of explanations with domain knowledge.",
    "As a result, objective, quantitative, and systematic assessment procedures are required (270)."
  ]
}